ZH: 我每天早上都会去公园碎步。
EN: I go for a brisk walk in the park every morning.

ZH: 运动前先做10分钟的碎步暖身。
EN: Warm up with a 10-minute brisk walk before exercising.

ZH: 慢跑者最好先从碎步开始。
EN: Beginner runners should start with brisk walking first.

ZH: 在没有电梯的情况下，登楼梯也可以当作碎步训练。
EN: Climbing stairs can be considered as a form of brisk walking workout when there is no elevator available.

ZH: 外出散步，选择碎步而不是漫步可以增加锻炼强度。
EN: Opting for a brisk walk instead of a leisurely stroll can increase exercise intensity when going out for a walk.

ZH: 每天晚饭后碎步一会有助于消化。
EN: Taking a brisk walk after dinner every day can help with digestion.

ZH: 他每天晚上碎步两圈，以保持健康。
EN: He takes two rounds of brisk walking every evening to stay healthy.

ZH: 临睡前的碎步可以帮助放松身心。
EN: A brisk walk before bedtime can help relax both the body and mind.

ZH: 碎步不仅可以增强心肺功能，还能够提高代谢。
EN: Brisk walking not only improves cardiovascular fitness but also boosts metabolism.

ZH: 出门碎步的时候，记得戴上运动鞋。
EN: Remember to wear athletic shoes when going out for a brisk walk.

ZH: 碎步可以帮助改善睡眠质量。
EN: Brisk walking can help improve the quality of sleep.

ZH: 忙碌的上班族可以利用午休时间碎步放松一下。
EN: Busy office workers can take a brisk walk during their lunch break to relax.

ZH: 碎步可以增加大脑的氧气供应，提高注意力。
EN: Brisk walking can increase oxygen supply to the brain and enhance focus.

ZH: 冬天也可以在室内碎步，例如在购物中心或者健身房中行走。
EN: During winter, indoor brisk walking can be done at places like shopping malls or fitness centers.

ZH: 长时间的久坐对健康不利，建议每小时碎步一番。
EN: Prolonged sitting is not good for health, it is recommended to take a brisk walk every hour.

ZH: 碎步可以帮助控制体重，燃烧额外的卡路里。
EN: Brisk walking can help control weight and burn extra calories.

ZH: 高血压患者可以通过每天碎步来降低血压。
EN: Patients with hypertension can lower their blood pressure by taking a daily brisk walk.

ZH: 环境优美的公园是碎步的理想场所。
EN: Beautiful parks are ideal places for brisk walking.

ZH: 每天增加碎步的时间，逐渐提升到30分钟以上。
EN: Increase the duration of brisk walking every day until reaching more than 30 minutes.

ZH: 碎步是一种简单而有效的有氧运动方式。
EN: Brisk walking is a simple yet effective aerobic exercise.
